             int serverPort,
             int clientPort)
      throws java.lang.InterruptedException,
             java.io.IOException
        Module representing the high-level of a vehicle.
        Parameters:
        startPoint - Starting point of the vehicle. Defined by input arguments of main method.
        serverPort - Port to listen for messages of SimKernel/Roskernel. Defined by input arguments of main method.
        clientPort - Port to send messages to SimKernel/Roskernel. Defined by input arguments of main method.

      • requestMap

        private void requestMap()
                 throws java.io.IOException
        REST GET request to Manager to request the name of the current map. If this map is not found in the offline available maps, it does another REST GET request to download the map files and store it in the mapfolder and add it to the maps.xml file. After that it sends this information to the vehicle SimKernel/SimKernel over the socket connection.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • updateRoute

        private void updateRoute()
        To be used when when a new waypoint has to be send to the vehicle or to check if route is completed. Sends information of the next waypoint over the socket connection to the vehicle's SimKernel/RosKernel.

      • wayPointReached

        private void wayPointReached()
        Event call over interface to be used when socket connection received message that waypoint has been reached.

      • routeCompleted

        private void routeCompleted()
        When all waypoints have been completed the vehicle becomes unoccupied again. Sends MQTT message to Manager to update the vehicle status.

      • routeError

        private void routeError()
        When all a requested route job can't be done by the vehicle. Sends MQTT message to Manager to update the route status.

      • routeNotComplete

        private void routeNotComplete()
        When all a requested route job can't be done by the vehicle as it's still completing a route. Sends MQTT message to Manager to update the route status.

      • sendWheelStates

        private void sendWheelStates(float throttle,
                             float steer)
        Send wheel states to the vehicle over the socket connection. useful for emergency stops and other specific requests.
        Parameters:
        throttle - throttle value for the vehicle wheels.
        steer - rotation value for the vehicle wheels.

      • locationUpdate

        private void locationUpdate(Location location)
        When vehicle's RosKernel/SimKernel sends update on route completion it needs to be transformed to the completion amount for the total route. To do this it receives a cost calculation from the RosServer that it requested and uses this to determine the size of each waypoint's sub-route.
        Parameters:
        location - Location object containing the current percentage value.

      • parseMQTT

        public void parseMQTT(java.lang.String topic,
                      java.lang.String message)
        Interfaced method to parse MQTT message and topic after MQTT callback is triggered by incoming message. Used by messages coming from Manager to request a route job or a cost calculation request.
        Specified by:
        parseMQTT in interface MQTTListener
        Parameters:
        topic - received MQTT topic
        message - received MQTT message string

      • parseTCP

        public java.lang.String parseTCP(java.lang.String message)
        Interfaced method to parse TCP message socket callback is triggered by incoming message. Used for messages about percentage route completion, next waypoint arrived, initial connection setup, stopping/killing/starting/restarting vehicle, setting the startpoint or cost calculation response.
        Specified by:
        parseTCP in interface TCPListener
        Parameters:
        message - received TCP socket message string
        Returns:
        a return answer to be send back over the socket to the SimKernel/RosKernel

      • sendAvailability

        private void sendAvailability(boolean state)
        Set availability status of vehicle in the Manager by sending MQTT message.
        Parameters:
        state - state to be send. (available=true, unavailable=false)

      • killCar

        private void killCar()
        Closes all connections (TCP & MQTT), unregisters the vehicle with the Manager and shut the module down.

      • costRequest

        private void costRequest(long[] wayPointIDs)
        Called by incoming cost calculation requests. Sends the request further to the RosKernel/SimKernel.
        Parameters:
        wayPointIDs - Array of waypoint ID's to have their cost calculated.

      • costComplete

        private void costComplete(Cost cost)
        Called by received response from SimKernel/RosKernel of cost calculation request.
        Parameters:
        cost - Cost object containing the calculated weights.

      • timeRequest

        private void timeRequest(long[] wayPointIDs)
        Called by incoming timing calculation requests. Sends the request further to the RosKernel/SimKernel.
        Parameters:
        wayPointIDs - Array of waypoint ID's to have their timing calculated.

      • timeComplete

        private void timeComplete(Cost cost)
        When vehicle has completed cost calculation for the locationUpdate() function it's sets the variables CostCurrentToStartTiming and CostStartToEndTiming of the Core to be used by locationUpdate().
        Parameters:
        cost - Cost object containing the weights of the sub-routes.

      • jobRequest

        private void jobRequest(long[] wayPointIDs)
        Event call over interface for when MQTT connection receives new route job requests from the Manager. Adds all requested waypoints to route queue one by one. Sets the vehicle to occupied. Ignores the request if vehicle is already occupied. Then triggers the first waypoint to be send to the RosKernel/SimKernel.
        Parameters:
        wayPointIDs - Array of waypoint ID's that are on the route to be completed.
